The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to automate the design of efficient neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on improving the efficiency of deep learning computing suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) and augmented reality (cs.AR) may also be relevant sub-categories. Additionally, the mention of hardware co-design and energy efficiency suggests that systems and control (cs.SY) may also be a relevant sub-category.
